    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Ilkley Wells ⇒ Any future letter to be addressed “Down Bromley Kent”</placeName>
                    <date>Dec. 4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>I am very much obliged for your note &amp; all the trouble you have so kindly taken about French Edition.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I have written to Mad. Belloc.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>I return papers signed &amp; witnessed.</p>
<p>I quite agree to all you say. &amp; do not care for extra copies of Kingsley’s sentence.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I am very glad of 3000 copies, but you must not run risk for my sake. I will not delay Printers.— I write briefly to save your time.—</p>
<p>Yours truly obliged | C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
